    },
    {
      "text": "Lauren McCutcheon",
      "url": "https://thephiladelphiacitizen.org/author/lauren-mccutcheon/"
    },
    {
      "text": "\n                        \n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t",
      "url": "https://thephiladelphiacitizen.org/christa-barfield-philadelphia/"
    },
    {
      "text": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\tGeneration Change Philly: The Urban Farmer\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tAn irrepressible leader of today\u2019s urban farming movement in Philadelphia, Christa Barfield builds individual and community health from the ground up\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tBy Christina Griffith\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t",
      "url": "https://thephiladelphiacitizen.org/christa-barfield-philadelphia/"
    },
    {
      "text": "\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\tA New College Conundrum \u2014 How\u2019s the Health Care?\t\tA long-time college president advises students and families to give careful attention in this post-Roe era to health care \u2014 especially reproductive and mental health care \u2014 on campus\n\t\t\tBy Elaine Maimon\t\n\t",
      "url": "https://thephiladelphiacitizen.org/college-health-care/"
    },
    {
      "text": "\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\tHow Philly Invented Ice Cream (As We Know It)\t\tIt was African American chefs who created the summertime treat we consume by the gallons, right here in the city where America was born\n\t\t\tBy Tonya Hopkins\t\n\t",
      "url": "https://thephiladelphiacitizen.org/philly-ice-cream-history/"
    },
    {
      "text": "\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\tIdeas We Should Steal Revisited: One Stop Contraception Shop\t\tWith Roe v. Wade overturned, a national nonprofit's work breaking down barriers to getting effective birth control is more vital than ever\n\t\t\tBy Jill Harkins\t\n\t",
      "url": "https://thephiladelphiacitizen.org/one-stop-contraception-shop/"
    },
    {
      "text": "\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\tFun Things to Do in Philly This Weekend\t\tBlobfest is back at Colonial Theatre, Movies On the Block returns with a screening of Black Panther, check out a Latin festival at Penn's Landing and more. \n\t\t\tBy Josh Middleton\t\n\t",
      "url": "https://thephiladelphiacitizen.org/things-to-do-philly-weekend/"
    },
    {
      "text": "\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\tSummer in Philadelphia\t\tFrom Pride through Made in America, the summer of 2022 invites Philly to join in\n\t\t\tBy Lauren McCutcheon and Josh Middleton\t\n\t",
      "url": "https://thephiladelphiacitizen.org/summer-philadelphia/"
    },
    {
      "text": "\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\tWomen\u2019s Choice, Men\u2019s Responsibility\t\tUntil the leaked draft decision that would eventually overturn Roe v. Wade, I had never told anyone \u2014 except my wife. \n\t\t\tBy Jay Coen Gilbert\t\n\t",
      "url": "https://thephiladelphiacitizen.org/womens-choice-mens-responsibility/"
    },
    {
      "text": "\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\tListen: This Fourth, \u201cRemember the Ladies\u201d\t\tCitizen Board Member and MSNBC host Ali Velshi invokes a letter by Abigail Adams to her husband, John, imploring him to remember women's rights when forming this country.\n\t\t\tBy Ali Velshi\t\n\t",
      "url": "https://thephiladelphiacitizen.org/listen-this-fourth-remember-the-ladies/"
    },
    {
      "text": "\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\tThe Fourth of July Thoughts We Need to Read Now\t\tJuly 4th means different things to different Americans. Here, a host of Independence Day perspectives \u2014 from Frederick Douglass, Susan B. Anthony, Ronald Reagan and more \u2014 that remind us what it means to be free\n\t\t\tBy Roxanne Patel Shepelavy\t\n\t",
      "url": "https://thephiladelphiacitizen.org/july-4-speeches/"
    },
